Definition: a schismatic Christian religion in northern Africa from the 4th to the 7th century
Example: held that only those who led a blameless life belonged in the church or could administer the sacraments
Synonyms: noun, person, donatist, Christianity, a, schismatic, Christian, religion, in, northern, Africa, from, the, th, to, century, held, that, only, those, who, led, blameless, life, belonged, church, or, could, administer, sacraments
Category: noun.cognition
